data.description: Welcome home to this beautiful two-story home in the highly desirable Orchard Hills Community. Like new 4 bedrooms, 2.5 bath Logan II floor plan with 2871 sqft Energy efficient home with its PAID OFF solar panels and propane tank. Just think of the savings you will have with an average power bill below $50.00 per month. You will fall in love with this home from the moment you pull up and notice your covered front porch with a seating area. Once you enter, you are greeted with beautiful laminate wood flooring throughout the main living area. To the right of the entrance, the private study would make the perfect home office. As you walk through the dining area you make your way into the open family and kitchen concept area. The family room has been prewired for sound in the ceiling for that ultimate sound experience. The kitchen features 42” cabinets with crown molding, tile backsplash, Tile flooring and granite countertops. You will love cooking with the propane stove being fueled from your inground propane tank. From there you can step out through your French doors into your extended covered and screened-in lanai where you will be able to enjoy a lovely sunset with NO rear neighbors. Once back inside you can visit the half bath near the garage entrance or make your way upstairs. The upper level features all four bedrooms, a large game room/loft, and a laundry room. A hallway bathroom with a dual sink quartz countertop and combo shower and tub. The spacious Master Suite features a large walk-in closet, dual sink quartz countertop along with a separate shower and tub. This home also features a home water softener system. Zoned for excellent neighborhood schools, including Keene’s Crossing Elementary and Bridgewater Middle School which are within walking/biking distance. Orchard Hills boasts resort-style features including an on-site fitness center, sparkling zero-entry pool, clubhouse with on-site property management, dog park and playgrounds and all of this is just steps away from your front door. Not to forget the elaborate community-hosted events including monthly food trucks, neighborhood scavenger searches, DJ pool parties, Winter snow slides, Foam parties, bingo and many other events both in-person and virtual throughout the year with its active social committee. HOA fee includes all yard maintenance as well. This community is centrally located just minutes away from the new Hamlin Lakeside Town Center, Fowlers Grove, Downtown Winter Garden, as well as the many popular theme park attractions that Orlando is famous for. With 429 just around the corner, it's easy to get to Downtown Orlando, the airport, and PLENTY of shopping. Don't miss this opportunity!
